<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Arrest Sonora Cartel Leader `El Moyo' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Arrest Sonora Cartel Leader `El Moyo' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2106183994 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2106183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In an incident described by the PGR [Attorney 
General's Office] as one of the harshest blows dealt to the drug 
trafficking mafia, on 15 June, authorities arrested Moises 
Juarez Ledezma, alias El Moyo and El Dienton, a key figure in 
the Sonora Cartel headed by Amado Carrillo Fuentes. El Moyo has 
been charged with crimes against public health, which include 
charges of funding, planting, cultivating, storing, and 
transporting drugs. 
  In the areas of Las Minitas and Las Trincheras in Sonora, 
which cover some 5,800 hectares, authorities confirmed the 
discovery of caps and jackets with bogus PGR and PJF [Federal 
Judicial Police] insignias, which were used by cartel members. 
  Meanwhile, the PGR also announced the 12 June arrest of 
Eduardo Salazar Carrillo, assistant PJF inspector in Sinaloa; 
Commander 2d Class Cesar Gomez Castaneda; and policemen Gilberto 
Barrios Barrios and Eric Escamilla Segovia. The four men are 
facing charges in connection with the possession of $306,921 in 
cash, several weapons used exclusively by the Army, and radio 
equipment. 

</TEXT>

