<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President-elect Ernesto Samper's campaign has just 
issued a communique regarding the contents of an audio cassette. 
On the tape, a well known Bogota journalist speaks to an 
alleged Cali Cartel leader. The conversation speaks of possible 
campaign contributions. Part of the communique says: 
  1. The President-elect talked today with the prosecutor 
general to request a swift and efficient investigation of the 
facts. Samper gave the prosecuter general's office his campaign 
accounting books for a thorough examination. 
  2. From the very beginning of the presidential campaign, we 
warned of the danger of drug trafficking money filtering into 
the political process. In response to this, a Code of Ethics 
was issued. This Code of Ethics contains a full chapter on 
controlling the source of campaign funding and it appoints an 
ethical prosecutor. 
  Former presidential candidate Andres Pastrana will address 
this controversial issue during a press conference tomorrow. 

