<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Executive Appoints New Integration Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Executive Appoints New Integration Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2106180094 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 17 Jun 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> PY2106180094 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The executive branch this morning named Ruben 
Melgarejo Lanzoni as political affairs secretary general and 
presidential private secretary. The decree also names Miguel 
Angel Maidana Zayas as presidential general secretary and civil 
household chief, and Hugo Saguier Caballero as integration 
minister. 
  The president, exercising his prerogative, created the new 
Political Affairs General Secretariat to handle the presidency's 
relations with political parties and movements. Secretary 
General Melgarejo Lanzoni is currently Paraguayan ambassador to 
the OAS in Washington. 
  Integration Minister Saguier Caballero was presidential 
secretary general and civil household chief while his successor, 
Maidana Zayas, was the presidential legal adviser. 
  Saguier Caballero replaces Atilio R. Fernandez who resigned 
recently to run for the presidency of the National Republican 
Association (ANR-Colorado Party). 
  Saguier Caballero is the fourth integration minister in less 
than three years. The first to head the newest of all ministries 
was Juan Carlos Wasmosy. He was replaced by Horacio Galeano 
Perrone, who was in turn replaced by Atilio R. Fernandez. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

