<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Asked To Probe Illegal Banking Activity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Asked To Probe Illegal Banking Activity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2106183794 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2106183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Attorney General's Office, through Prosecutors 
Dumer C. Monzon and Josefina Itriago, has asked 21st Penal Court 
Judge Cibeliz Duran to investigate alleged illegal activities 
that may have prompted the eight banks in which the government 
has intervened to go bankrupt. The inquiry will not conflict 
with the 26th Penal Court's investigation because it will deal 
with the manner in which government financial assistance was 
used. 
  Meanwhile, the Superior Court for the Protection of Public 
Property [TSS] has also initiated an investigation into alleged 
irregularities at the eight banks. The Superior Council of 
Judges must decide whether the case falls under the jurisdiction 
of the TSS or whether Judge Duran should hear the case. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

