<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Executive Instructs Fogade To Pay Depositors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Executive Instructs Fogade To Pay Depositors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2106141294 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2106141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The executive branch has instructed Fogade [Deposit 
Guarantee and Banking Protection Fund] to immediately pay up to 
4 million bolivares to depositors of the eight banks intervened 
by government decree, in accordance with Article 23 of the 
special law protecting depositors and regulating emergencies at 
banking institutions. 
  The measure was adopted at a special Council of Ministers 
meeting at Miraflores Palace, where the issue was examined in 
barely 10 minutes. The ministers interpreted the text of the 
law, according to which it is not possible to wait until the 
banks in question are rehabilitated or their debts settled to 
return depositors' funds. 
  The announcement was made by Finance Minister Julio Sosa 
Rodriguez, who said the 13-article decree explains the 
situation. Sosa has announced the General Bank Superintendency, 
Fogade, and the interveners of the eight banks, who were 
discussing payment schedules, have already been notified of this 
decision. 
  [Begin Sosa recording] Payment of the 4 million bolivares 
will begin, to the extent possible, on 27 June. The depositors 
are entitled to 4 million bolivares whether a bank is liquidated 
or rehabilitated, and there is no reason to subject them to 
delays of up to 30 days, which is how long it takes to make that 
decision. There is no reason to subject depositors to that 
deadline. [end recording] 
  Sosa has denied the wave of rumors concerning alleged crises 
at other banks. He said such remarks are unfounded and greatly 
harm the country. Sosa has urged the Venezuelan people not to 
spread such rumors because foreigners, willing to invest in the 
country, purchase Venezuelan Government and private 
institutions' assets when conditions are good and a good effort 
could be wasted. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-34627 </DOCNO>
