<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fidel Castro Meets With Canadian Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fidel Castro Meets With Canadian Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2106160194 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1402 GMT 
21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2106160194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commander in Chief Fidel Castro met with Christine 
Stewart, Canada's minister of state for Latin America and 
Africa. Sources from Canada's delegation confirmed that Stewart 
has also met with Carlos Lage, vice president of the council of 
ministers, Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina, and other high 
ranking government officials. A spokesmen from Canada's Foreign 
Ministry informed the media that this is the most important 
moment in relations between Cuba and Canada. 
  On 20 June, Canada reported the resumption of official 
economic aid to Cuba. Canada also reported that $370,000 
[country of currency not specified] in food products for 
children will be given to Cuba this year and $720,000 in 1995. 
The decision was announced simultaneously in Ottawa by Canada's 
Minister of Foreign Affairs Andre Ouellet and in Havana by 
Christine Stewart, who concludes a two-day visit to Cuba today. 

</TEXT>

