<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Comments on NAFTA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Minister Comments on NAFTA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2206001794 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 1850 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2206001794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Eduardo Aninat has said 
negotiations with the United States over an eventual free trade 
treaty should start in September or October of this year. 
  Aninat said Chile will wait until the U.S. Congress empowers 
President Clinton to negotiate such an agreement. He added that 
official negotiations will be undertaken immediately after this. 
  He explained that the Chilean Government will consult all 
national sectors prior to signing any agreement. He added that 
after assessing the impact of a trade agreement on the Chilean 
economy, the government will decide whether to negotiate a 
bilateral agreement with the United States or join NAFTA. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

