<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Lula, Cardoso as Runoff Contenders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Lula, Cardoso as Runoff Contenders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2106133494 Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 
17 Jun 94 p A6 </F>

<F P=103> PY2106133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo O ESTADO DE SAO PAULO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The latest poll by Gallup Institute was 
conducted between 4 and 15 June. It was conducted exclusively 
for O ESTADO. It reveals that if the presidential elections were 
held today, there would be a runoff election. Those polled were 
shown the list of candidates. PT [Workers Party] candidate Luiz 
Inacio Lula da Silva and PSDB [Brazilian Social Democracy Party] 
candidate Fernando Henrique Cardoso received 37.9 and 22.8 
percent, respectively, of the votes. This shows that they would 
have to participate in a runoff election. 
  These percentages for the two main candidates are very 
similar to the ones in the previous poll. Compared to last 
month's poll, the popularity of Lula and Cardoso dropped by 0.4 
and 0.7 percent, respectively. [passage omitted] 
  As for the other candidates, Leonel Brizola obtained 7.6 
percent, Orestes Quercia received 6.8 percent, Esperidiao Amin 
received 2.5 percent, Eneas Carneiro received 2.0 percent, and 
Flavio Rocha received 1.1 percent. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

