<F P=106> [From the "Exclusive" program] </F>
  [Text] Marcelino dos Santos, Mozambique's Assembly 
president, said during a news conference that there is an 
historic demand for Frelimo [Mozambique Liberation Front] to win 
the elections and there is no possibility that its main 
opposition, Renamo [Mazambique National Resistance], could wage 
a war as UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola] did in Angola after the elections. 
  Dos Santos also said the conditions under which his country 
will celebrate its national holiday on 25 June. Dos Santos 
stressed that he was in Cuba to learn firsthand the situation 
there and the manner in which the people are ready to resist and 
triumph. 
  [Begin Dos Santos recording, in Portuguese] I would like to 
express our complete solidarity with the Republic of Cuba. We 
must fight this international illegality, the economic blockade 
against Cuba, which is an international bastion. 
  Let us not forget that the peoples of the world need Cuba to 
remain firm, and that it is important for the progress of all 
peoples. Furthermore, I would say the victory of the Cuban 
people is necessary for all the peoples of the world. [end 
recording] 

