<H3> <TI>   GRANMA Discusses Production of Cigarettes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    GRANMA Discusses Production of Cigarettes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2206155994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1408 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2206155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 22 June, GRANMA reported that producing 60 
million cigarettes a day satisfies the demand for regulated and 
extra quotas, as well as unregulated sales of cigarettes. The 
article cites the Agriculture Ministry's tobacco enterprise 
union as saying that the eight cigarettes factories are at full 
production capacity. The article points out that 14,468,900 
packs of cigarettes were distributed to the population between 1 
June -- when cigarette sales were deregulated -- and 16 June. 
The demand for unregulated cigarettes on the national market, 
initially high, has decreased. This has helped market stability. 

</TEXT>

