<F P=106> [From the "First Thing" program] </F>
  [Text] The Havana City water shortage is primarily due to a 
decrease in the level of the phreatic layer of the Vento Basin 
and multiple pump breakdowns. Water service authorities have 
reported that the Havana City municipalities most affected by 
these shortages include: Centro Habana, Habana Vieja, Cerro, 
and Plaza de la Revolucion. 

