<H3> <TI>   Army Tries To Confirm Capture of Top EPL Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Tries To Confirm Capture of Top EPL Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2206193394 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1612 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2206193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Francisco Caraballo, the top EPL [People's 
Liberation Army] leader and one of the most wanted guerrillas in 
the country, reportedly was captured near Santa Fe de Bogota a 
few hours ago. 
  Emisoras Caracol Network has learned that in an operation 
conducted near the capital -- either in Chia or Cajic -- seven 
people, including Caraballo, were apprehended. The Army, with 
the assistance of the National Registrar's Office, is now 
attempting to confirm whether the captured individual is indeed 
Caraballo. A news conference will be held within the next few 
hours by the 13th Infantry Brigade to report on the details of 
this operation. 
  Caraballo, who was active in Cordoba and Antioquia's Uraba 
region, has long been involved in the EPL's war against 
Patriotic Unity in Uraba. He is Fidel Castano's No. 1 enemy 
and, we reiterate, one of the Colombian Army's most wanted 
guerrillas. 

</TEXT>

