<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on Arrest of EPL Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Arrest of EPL Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2306014694 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2306014694 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Alvaro Ayala from the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Army has arrested guerrilla leader Francisco 
Caraballo, top leader of the People's Liberation Army [EPL], who 
was being sought by authorities, 10 minutes from Santa Fe de 
Bogota. 
  Troops headed by General Norberto Adrada Cordoba arrested 
top 
EPL leader Francisco Caraballo. The Army mounted an 
intelligence operation two years ago because they knew he had to 
come to Cajiga to visit his wife and son. He arrived last night 
and was arrested this morning. 
  [Begin recording] [Caraballo] When I became a guerrilla, the 
possibilities for joining a legal political movement with the 
opportunity of being a political opposition were closed. 
  [Unidentified reporter] Why did you murder the 
surgeon-priest? 
  [Caraballo] I did not murder him. 
  [Reporter] Why did you order his murder? 
  [Caraballo] I did not order him killed. 
  [Reporter] But you never wanted peace, and you have shown 
you 
do not want peace. 
  [Caraballo] I disagree with that. 
  [Gen. Hernan Jose Guzman] This is a hard blow to the 
guerrillas because in less than 15 days, the Army has arrested 
their commander, their third person in command, and other 
members of the organization. We have also arrested Genaro [not 
further identified], who was the coordinator of their 
activities. [end recording] 
  The arrest of guerrilla leader Francisco Caraballo was the 
result of an intelligence operation conducted by the Colombian 
Army; no reward was paid. 

</TEXT>

