<H3> <TI>   Popular Christian Party Secretary General Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Popular Christian Party Secretary General Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2206192394 Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 10 Jun 94 p A5 </F>
<F P=103> PY2206192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima EL COMERCIO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, Congressman Antero Flores Araoz assumed, 
for the second time, the Collegiate General Secretariat of the 
Popular Christian Party (PPC) replacing Alberto Borea Odria who 
resigned. 
  Flores Araoz said he accepted the secretariat in compliance 
with party internal regulations but called for complementary 
internal elections as soon as possible to fill vacancies. 
  In accordance with party regulations, Florez Araoz, Lourdes 
Flores Cano, and Ricardo Amiel Meza are PPC leaders. Flores 
Araoz was installed by PPC President Luis Bedoya Reyes in the 
presence of the entire Enlarged Political Committee. 

</TEXT>

