<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   500 Arrested, 1 Killed in Carabobo Riots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    500 Arrested, 1 Killed in Carabobo Riots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2206233794 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2206233794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Riots in Carabobo State left one person dead, 
hundreds injured, three police agents wounded, two trucks 
burned, and 500 people arrested. 
  [Begin reporter Xiomara Gallardo recording] The riots 
started 
at the end of a march held as part of a day of civic 
demonstrations, which took place today to protest price 
speculation and increases in public services rates. The National 
Guard and the Carabobo State Police intervened in the riots and 
militarized the city's main streets. Police Chief Osvaldo 
Barreto said the situation is already under control. [end 
recording] 
  Meanwhile, there was a new wave of protests at the Central 
University of Venezuela this afternoon. 
  [Begin reporter Florisol Suarez recording] Masked university 
students again clashed with the Metropolitan Police after a 
truck belonging to the Caracas Electrical Company was burned. 
There was even a shootout between police agents and masked 
students; no one was injured. The Rinoceronte, an armored 
vehicle, arrived at the scene of the shootout. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

