<H3> <TI>   Caldera Orders Release of 2d Coup Attempt Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Caldera Orders Release of 2d Coup Attempt Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2206171894 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 
21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2206171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Rafael Caldera has ordered the release of 
General Francisco Visconti, leader of the second coup attempt 
who was in exile in Peru for more than a year. 
  Visconti has received the presidential pardon in exchange 
for 
a discharge from the Armed Forces as part of the conditions the 
government had demanded to approve the pardon. 

</TEXT>

