<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accords Signed With Portugal To Broaden Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Accords Signed With Portugal To Broaden Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2206215994 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 
19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2206215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" Newscast] </F>
  [Text] Portugal and Venezuela have broadened even more 
their bilateral ties with the signing of three agreements that 
will be used as a frame of reference for future negotiations 
between the two countries. 
  At the meeting held at the Yellow House, Portuguese Prime 
Minister Anibal Cavaco Silva and Venezuelan President Rafael 
Caldera signed three agreements on reciprocal investment 
promotion and protection; cooperation; and prevention, control, 
supervision, and suppression of illegal consumption and 
trafficking of drugs and psychotropic substances. 
  The Portuguese prime minister explained Portugal chose 
Venezuela to broaden ties with because Portugal believes 
Venezuela is one of the Latin American countries with the 
largest credibility. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

