<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Riots Erupt in Moron, Puerto Cabello; Students Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Riots Erupt in Moron, Puerto Cabello; Students Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2206195894 Paris AFP in Spanish 1805 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2206195894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moron, Venezuela, 22 Jun (AFP) -- Riots, during 
which two grocery stores were looted, rocked Moron and Puerto 
Cabello today. Meanwhile, student protests were staged in 
Caracas. 
  The disturbances took place in Moron after a march was 
called 
to protest the high cost of living, but the situation is already 
under control, according to statements to the media by Governor 
Henrique Salas. Similar protests were staged in nearby Puerto 
Cabello. 
  Valencia--the country's third largest city located 100 km 
west of Caracas--was left without bus service because of a 
strike. Drivers are demanding higher bus fares, according to the 
governor. 
  Around noon, protests were staged near the Central 
University 
of Venezuela in Caracas, and local journalists reported that 
police had arrived on the scene. 

</TEXT>

