<F P=102>   PY2406004994 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
23 Jun 94 p B3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2406004994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Danuza" column by Maria Clara Jorge and Mariza </F>
Louven] 
  [Text] Federal Deputy Sidney de Miguel (Green Party-Rio de 
Janeiro) is investigating a charge raised by a biology professor 
in Angra dos Reis, who claims to have detected signs of 
contamination in children residing in the Angra dos Reis 
municipal district and in employees of the Angra-1 nuclear plant. 
  The biology professor has noted the emergence of cysts; 
ovarian, breast, and uterine cancer; and even reduction in 
chromosomes in some children. 
  Deputy de Miguel has asked the attorney general to shut down 
the nuclear plant until the true cause of these health disorders 
is determined. 

