<H3> <TI>   President-Elect: Ties With Japan `Top Priority' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President-Elect: Ties With Japan `Top Priority' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2306125294 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 21 Jun 94 
Evening Edition p 4 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2306125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Yoshinori Nakai] </F>
  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 21 Jun -- On 20 June, Colombian 
President-elect Ernesto Samper and Vice President-elect Humberto 
de la Calle held their first news conference for the foreign 
press, including MAINICHI SHINBUN. Touching on economic 
relations, the president-elect said: "Colombia will give top 
priority to our relations with Japan, and we want Japan to know 
more about our country." 
  Concerning the current lack of interest among Japanese 
companies toward investing in Colombia due to apprehensions over 
security problems such as terrorism and abduction, both of them 
pointed out: "Other foreign investors share the same anxieties. 
Since measures have been taken to ensure security, however, 
such activities are no obstacle to investment." They also said: 
"We hope the Japanese people will try to learn more about 
Colombia. We are sure that measures can be taken to solve the 
security problem." 

</TEXT>

