<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Plan To Control Refugees Viewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Plan To Control Refugees Viewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2406042994 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0125 GMT 24 Jun 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2406042994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington, 23 Jun (PL) -- The U.S. Federal 
Government and the Florida State Government will implement a 
program intended to control the massive flow of refugees to the 
coasts of this southern U.S. state. 
  U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno made this announcement 
today. She did not provide the details of this operation, 
called Short Distance, however. She said the operation is still 
being prepared. 
  Reno pointed out that details of the operation are being 
coordinated with Florida Governor Lawton Chiles and that the 
operation will be implemented promptly with the support of the 
Pentagon and other government organizations. 
  According to its designers in the Justice Department, the 
Short Distance operation is intended to help the coastal states, 
especially Florida, control the entrance of refugees coming 
mainly from Haiti and Cuba. 
  According to reports, concentration centers will be set up 
and the Army and other government agencies will provide 
provisions, while asylum applications are being processed. 

</TEXT>

