<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice Foreign Minister Allende Visits Austria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Foreign Minister Allende Visits Austria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2306222394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2306222394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Radio News"] </F>
  [Text] Since 21 June, Vice Foreign Minister Isabel Allende 
has been in Austria, where she has met with several politicians 
and members of parliament. Cuban diplomatic sources in Vienna 
advised that Allende has met with the Austrian interim foreign 
minister, and with political, economic, and European integration 
officials. 
  Allende also met with members of parliament and relayed to 
Heinz Fischer, president of the Nationalrat, Ricardo Alarcon's 
invitation to visit Cuba. Allende also held an affable meeting 
with members of the Cuban-Austrian Friendship Association. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-34762 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat122_a_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-122 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  24 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Deny Visa to Opposition Figure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Deny Visa to Opposition Figure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2406041694 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2151 GMT 24 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2406041694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 23 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Opposition figure Rafael 
Gutirrez Santos protested today the fact that Cuban authorities 
refuse to give him permission to leave Cuba to attend an 
international trade union meeting in Brussels, Belgium. 
Gutirrez Santos, who is 58 years old, is on probation after 
spending eight months in prison for charges of spreading "enemy 
propaganda." His sentence is still pending. 
  The activist showed foreign journalists the invitation sent 
to him by the International Conference of Free Trade Union 
Organizations (CIOSL), which is headquartered in Brussels, to 
participate in a forum on human and labor rights to be held next 
week. 
  The Belgian Government informed CIOSL that it would grant a 
visa to Gutirrez Santos but Cuban authorities have refused to 
renew his passport and to grant him a corresponding departure 
permit, Gutirrez Santos said. 
  Gutirrez Santos was an electromechanical operator in the 
port 
of Havana and a leader of a regional merchant marine union, 
which is affiliated with the Cuban Workers Federation until 1992 
when he was expelled from the union for his opposition 
activities. He was also fired from his job at that time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

