<H3> <TI>   Government Establishes Visa Requirement for Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Establishes Visa Requirement for Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2406023694 Paris AFP in Spanish 0145 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2406023694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Port-au-Prince, 23 Jun (AFP) -- This Thursday, the 
provisional government of President Emile Jonassaint (not 
recognized by the international community) established a visa 
requirement for foreign citizens whose countries demand visas 
from Haitian citizens. This measure particularly affects U.S. 
and Canadian citizens, who until now did not need visas to enter 
Haiti. 
  A government communique stated that a $50 tax will also be 
required of foreigners entering Haiti. Foreigners will be able 
to obtain visas at ports and airports in the country. 

</TEXT>

