<H3> <TI>   FRAPH Cancels Call for 24 Jun General Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRAPH Cancels Call for 24 Jun General Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2306213594 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2306213594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Armed Revolutionary Front of the Haitian People, 
formerly the Revolutionary Front for the Promotion and Progress 
of Haiti [FRAPH], has canceled their call for a strike on 
Friday, 24 June. There are many reasons for this decision, the 
spokesman for the Front stated. The academic year-end exams, the 
deadline for the U.S. sanctions to go into effect, the fact that 
the population might like to get fresh supplies, the fact that 
some people, including both Haitians and foreigners, should 
leave the country before the suspension of the commercial 
flights scheduled for Saturday, 25 June, are among the reasons 
that prompted the Front officials to withdraw their call for a 
strike, according to its spokesman. 

</TEXT>

