<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Agreement With Japan to Be Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cooperation Agreement With Japan to Be Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2406040494 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2406040494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Education Secretary Jose Angel Pescador Osuna 
inaugurated the Fourth National Conference of Industrial and 
Technological School Directors. Pescador indicated that 
technological training is as fundamental as basic education. 
  [Begin Pescador recording] Aside from Mexico's fundamental 
objective of advancing its basic education through a national 
program, our hopes for the future might best be met by promoting 
technological training and research. [end recording] 
  Raul Gonzalez, director general for industrial and 
technological training, announced the guidelines for the school 
period beginning in September. Raul Panan, deputy secretary for 
technological training and research, announced that Mexico and 
Japan will sign a cooperation agreement to create the national 
teachers' training center in July. The Japanese Government will 
supply machinery and high-tech equipment. The General 
Directorate of Industrial and Technological Education includes 
424 schools and 403,000 students throughout the country. 

</TEXT>

