<F P=106> [Report by Esteban Huertas G.] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Jose Raul Mulino announced 
yesterday Panama will establish special flights for Haitians who 
are in Panamanian territory when the blockade on commercial 
flights to that Caribbean island goes into effect. 
  Mulino said that before that date, "Haitians who are in the 
country may be returned to their country." 
  The foreign minister added that if Haitian citizens cannot 
get seats on "scheduled Copa flights to Haiti for any reason, 
the Panamanian authorities will authorize the airline to make 
two flights so that all of the Haitians may return home. [no 
closing quotation mark as published] 

