<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 23 Jun (EFE) -- Cuban State security has 
summoned several human rights activists for questioning on their 
alleged cooperation with those individuals inside the residence 
of the Belgian ambassador in Havana, a dissident source said 
today. 
  Among those summoned to "Villa Maristas," which is the 
general headquarters of Cuban State security in Havana, are 
Elizardo Sanchez and Vladimiro Roca, both members of the 
"Democratic Socialist Current," and Jesus Yanes Pelletier of the 
"Cuban Human Rights Committee." 
  The dissident source explained they had been summoned by 
authorities for questioning on their alleged connection with the 
Cubans occupying the Belgian diplomatic mission. The source, 
however, affirmed they do not know those who are inside the 
Belgian diplomatic mission, adding that they could be 
independent human rights activists. 

