<H3> <TI>   Cuban Legislators Meet Vice President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuban Legislators Meet Vice President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2306155594 Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 23 Jun 94 p 18 </F>
<F P=103> PY2306155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion NOTICIAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Cuban congressional delegation that is visiting 
our country met on 22 June with Chamber of Deputies President 
Francisco Jose De Vargas and congressional Public Health 
Committee members. 
  The delegation of representatives from the National Assembly 
of the People's Government [ANPP] is made up of Carlos Dotres 
Martinez and Sergio Pastrana, chairman and secretary of the ANPP 
Health, Sport, and Environment Committee, respectively. They are 
being accompanied by Manuel Samora, a Central Committee 
International Department member. 
  During the meeting the legislators discussed strengthening 
links between legislators from the two nations through an 
exchange of experiences. 
  The Cuban legislators recalled that last year a delegation 
of 
National Congress Health Committee members visited Havana, 
adding that they had an opportunity to personally get acquainted 
with the progress achieved in this field by Fidel Castro's 
administration. 
  At the end of the meeting with Deputy De Vargas the Cuban 
delegation visited the Clinic Hospital and then met Vice 
President Angel Roberto Seifart. The Cuban delegation also will 
visit historic and tourist attractions. The delegation will stay 
in the country until 26 June. 

