<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Specialist Hails ACS Formation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Specialist Hails ACS Formation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2406200894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2406200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Radio News"] </F>
  [Text] Omar Morales, a Foreign Ministry specialist, has 
told PRENSA LATINA that plans to form the Association of 
Caribbean States, ACS, reflect the spirit of convergence among 
today's approaches to Latin American integration. Morales said 
this is very healthy for the hemisphere because it opens the way 
to a degree of economic unity that will put the hemisphere in a 
more advantageous position to negotiate with other regional 
groups in the world. 
  The ACS will include three regional blocs: the Caribbean 
Common Market, CARICOM; the Secretariat of Central American 
Economic Integration, SIECA; and the G-3, which includes Mexico, 
Venezuela, and Colombia. Morales also said that heads of state 
of the member countries will meet in the Barbadian capital on 4 
July to establish the ACS, an intergovernmental organization for 
regional teamwork, consultation, and cooperation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

